collabtxt	La base de donnée FLOW est enregistrée dans le Biodiversity Information Networks Database du TDWG (Biodiversity Information Standards).\r\n\r\nFLOW est une contribution au projet BEFRI (Biodiversity and Evolution of Fulgoromorpha, a global Research Initiative), une initiative d'un groupe informel d'experts sur les Fulgoromorphes.\r\n\r\nAu titre de référentiel taxonomique, FLOW a participé au projet Species 2000-Europa financé par le 5e programme cadre (Cordis) de la Commission Européenne (2003-2006). FLOW participa aussi aux projets 4D4Life (Distributed Dynamic Diversity Databases for Life) et i4Life financés par le 7e programme cadre de la Commission Europénne (Research Infrastructures INFRA-2008-1.2.2 - Scientific Data Infrastructures) (2009-2012). Par ces projets, FLOW fournit ses données au programme Catalogue of Life (CoL).\r\n\r\nA travers CoL, FLOW sert ainsi de référentiel taxonomique pour les Fulgores à diverses initiatives globales et Européennes comme au GBIF (Global Biodiversity Information Facility), EoL, (Encyclopedy of Life), Genbank, CBoL (Barcode of Life), … Enfin, la base est aussi publiée annuellement sous la forme un CD-ROM gratuit dans l'Annual Check List du 'Species 2000 & ITIS Catalogue of Life'.	FLOW database is registered in the Biodiversity Information Networks Database of the Biodiversity Information Standards (TDWG), and is part of the BEFRI project (Biodiversity and Evolution of Fulgoromorpha, a global Research Initiative), an initiative of an informal planthopper specialist group.\r\n\r\nAs a global systematic database (GSD), FLOW was involved in the Species 2000-Europa project supported by the European Commission under the 5th framework programme (Cordis) (2003-2006). It contributed to the 4D4Life project (Distributed Dynamic Diversity Databases for Life), and i4Life two projects of the European Commission's e-Infrastructure Programme, itself part of the Capacities Programme of Framework 7 (2009-2012). Through these projects, FLOW provides its data to the Catalogue of Life project (CoL).\r\n\r\nSubsequently, FLOW serves as the taxonomic backbone provided by the CoL for the planthopper systematics to the GBIF (Global Biodiversity Information Facility), EoL (Encyclopedy of Life), Genbank, CBoL (Barcode of Life), and several others global or European initiatives … FLOW data are also available on a free CD-ROM: Annual Check List of the 'Species 2000 & ITIS Catalogue of Life'.	El proyecto FLOW se cita en el Biodiversity Information Networks Database de TDWG (Biodiversity Information Standards). Esta conectado con otros EU-proyectos y es accesible usando las portadas como la de Species 2000 & ITIS Dynamic Checklist of the Catalogue of Life (CoL) , la del  Global Biodiversity Information Facility (GBIF)  o la del Encyclopedy of Life, (EoL) . Tambien se puede tener la on un CD-ROM gratuito : el Annual Check List  del 'Species 2000 & ITIS Catalogue of Life'.	A base de dados FLOW está registrada no Biodiversity Information Networks Database do Biodiversity Information Standards (TDWG),  e é parte do projeto BEFRI  (Biodiversity and Evolution of Fulgoromorpha, a global Research Initiative), uma iniciativa de um grupo informal de especialistas em Fulgoromorpha. \r\n\r\nComo uma base de dados sistemática global (GSD, do inglês Global Systematic Database), o FLOW esteve envolvido  no projeto Species 2000-Europa, financiado pelo 5° programa estrutural (Cordis) da Comissão Européia (2003-2006). FLOW participo do projetos 4D4Life (Distributed Dynamic Diversity Databases for Life) y i4Life, financiado pelo 7° Programa Estrutural da Comissão Européia (Research Infrastructures INFRA-2008-1.2.2 - Scientific Data Infrastructures) (2009-2012). Por estes projetos, o FLOW fornece seus dados ao projeto Catalog of Life (CoL).\r\nAtravés do CoL, o FLOW serve, consequentemente, como referencial taxonômico para sistemática de Fulgoromorpha para o GBIF (Global Biodiversity Information Facility), EoL (Encyclopedy of Life), Genbank, CBoL (Barcode of Life), e várias outras iniciativas globais ou européias. Os dados do FLOW também estão disponíveis em CD-ROM: Annual Check List of the 'Species 2000 & ITIS Catalogue of Life'.\r\n	FLOW database is registered in the Biodiversity Information Networks Database of the Biodiversity Information Standards (TDWG), and is part of the BEFRI project (Biodiversity and Evolution of Fulgoromorpha, a global Research Initiative), an initiative of an informal planthopper specialist group.\r\n\r\nAs a global systematic database (GSD), FLOW was involved in the Species 2000-Europa project supported by the European Commission under the 5th framework programme (Cordis) (2003-2006). It contributed to the 4D4Life project (Distributed Dynamic Diversity Databases for Life), and i4Life two projects of the European Commission's e-Infrastructure Programme, itself part of the Capacities Programme of Framework 7 (2009-2012). Through these projects, FLOW provides its data to the Catalogue of Life project (CoL).\r\n\r\nSubsequently, FLOW serves as the taxonomic backbone provided by the CoL for the planthopper systematics to the GBIF (Global Biodiversity Information Facility), EoL (Encyclopedy of Life), Genbank, CBoL (Barcode of Life), and several others global or European initiatives … FLOW data are also available on a free CD-ROM: Annual Check List of the 'Species 2000 & ITIS Catalogue of Life'.	anta	2007-01-16	bourgoin	2014-11-15	FLOW database is registered in the Biodiversity Information Networks Database of the Biodiversity Information Standards (TDWG), and is part of the BEFRI project (Biodiversity and Evolution of Fulgoromorpha, a global Research Initiative), an initiative of an informal planthopper specialist group.\r\n\r\nAs a global systematic database (GSD), FLOW was involved in the Species 2000-Europa project supported by the European Commission under the 5th framework programme (Cordis) (2003-2006). It contributed to the 4D4Life project (Distributed Dyna