inc_economic_interest	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p>Les Cercopoidea sont reconnus pour se nourrir de xyl&egrave;me. Leurs plantes h&ocirc;tes sont nombreuses et ils infligent des pertes importantes sur certaines cultures et ceci dans le monde entier.</p>\r\n<p>Au sein de la famille des Cercopidae le genre Locris Stål, 1866 est connu pour ses espèces faisant des ravages en Afrique. En Amérique du Sud et centrale, d’autres espèces sont responsables de dégâts sur pâturages (Mello et al., 1996 ; Holmann & Peck, 2002) mais aussi sur canne à sucre, avec des pertes s’élevant jusqu’à 70% dans des régions infestées (Thompson, 2004).</p>\r\n<p>Certaines espèces du genre Hindola Kirkaldy, 1900 (Machaerotidae) sont des vecteurs de bactéries affectant les girofliers en Indonésie (Eden-Green, 1986). L'espèce Philaenus spumarius (Aphrophoridae) d'origine européenne s'inscrit également parmi les espèces d’intérêts économiques et tout particulièrement depuis qu'elle a été introduite aux USA et en Nouvelle-Zélande.</p>\r\n</div>	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p> The Cercopoidea is known to feed on xylem. Their host plants are numerous and they inflict important losses on certain cultures and this all over the world..</p>\r\n<p>Within the Cercopidae the genus Locris Stål, 1866 is known for being an important pest in Africa. In South America some species are responsable for damages on pastures (Mello et al., 1996 ; Holmann & Peck, 2002) but also on sugar cane for which the loss can reach 70% in the infested regions (Thompson, 2004).</p>\r\n<p>Some species of the genus Hindola Kirkaldy, 1900 (Machaerotidae) are vectors of bacteria affecting clove trees in Indonesia (Eden-Green, 1986). The species Philaenus spumarius (Aphrophoridae) of european origin is of economic interests especially since it was introduced in the USA and New Zealand.</p>\r\n</div>	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p>Cercopoidea son reconocidos para alimentarse de xyleme. Sus plantas hu&eacute;spedes son numerosos y ellos infligen p&eacute;rdidas importantes sobre ciertas culturas y esto en el mundo entero.</p>\r\n<p>En el seno de la familia de Cercopidae el g&eacute;nero Locris St&aring;l, 1866 es conocido por sus especies que causan estragos en Africa. En Am&eacute;rica del Sur y la central, otras especies son responsables de da&ntilde;os sobre pastos (Mello y al., 1996; Holmann y Peck, 2002) pero tambi&eacute;n sobre ca&ntilde;a de az&uacute;car, con p&eacute;rdidas que se elevan hasta el 70 % en regiones infestadas (Thompson, 2004).</p>\r\n<p>Ciertas especies del g&eacute;nero Hindola Kirkaldy, 1900 (Machaerotidae) son unos vectores de bacterias que afectan los claveros en Indonesia (Eden-green, 1986). La especie Philaenus spumarius (Aphrophoridae) de origen europeo tambi&eacute;n se inscribe entre las especies de intereses econ&oacute;micos y muy particularmente desde que ha sido introducida a USA y en Nueva Zelanda.</p>\r\n</div>	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p>Os Cercopoidea são conhecidos por se alimentarem de xilema. Suas plantas hospedeiras são numerosas e eles infligem perdas importantes sobre certas culturas, por todo o planeta. </p>\r\n<p>No seio da família Cercopidae, o gênero Locris  Stål, 1866 é conhecido por suas espécies que causam importantes estragos na África. Nas Américas do Sul e Central, outras espécies são responsáveis por danos em pastagens (Mello et al., 1996; Holmann & Peck, 2002) e também em cana de açúcar, com perdas que se elevam a até 70% em regiões afetadas. (Thompson, 2004).</p>\r\n<p>Certas espécies do gênero Hindola Kirkaldy, 1900 (Machaerotidae) são vetores de bactérias que afetam os craveiros na Indonésia (Eden-green, 1986). A espécie Philaenus spumarius (Aphrophoridae), de origem européia, também se encontra entre as espécies de interesse econômico, especialmente depois que foi introduzida nos EUA e Nova Zelândia.</p>\r\n</div>	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p> The Cercopoidea is known to feed on xylem. Their host plants are numerous and they inflict important losses on certain cultures and this all over the world..</p>\r\n<p>Within the Cercopidae the genus Locris Stål, 1866 is known for being an important pest in Africa. In South America some species are responsable for damages on pastures (Mello et al., 1996 ; Holmann & Peck, 2002) but also on sugar cane for which the loss can reach 70% in the infested regions (Thompson, 2004).</p>\r\n<p>Some species of the genus Hindola Kirkaldy, 1900 (Machaerotidae) are vectors of bacteria affecting clove trees in Indonesia (Eden-Green, 1986). The species Philaenus spumarius (Aphrophoridae) of european origin is of economic interests especially since it was introduced in the USA and New Zealand.</p>\r\n</div>	soulier	2011-04-14	bourgoin	2014-02-03	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p> The Cercopoidea is known to feed on xylem. Their host plants are numerous and they inflict important losses on certain cultures and this all over the world..</p>\r\n<p>Within the Cercopidae the genus Locris Stål, 1866 is known for being an important pest in Africa. In South America some species are responsable for damages on pastures (Mello et al., 1996 ; Holmann & Peck, 2002) but also on sugar cane for which the loss can reach 70% in the infested regions (Thompson, 2004).</p>\r\n<p>Some species of the genus Hindola Kirkaldy, 1900 (Machaerotidae) are vectors of bacteria affecting clove trees in Indonesia (Eden-Green, 1986). The species Philaenus spumarius (Aphrophoridae) of european origin is of economic interests especially since it was introduced in the USA and New Z