techtxt	Cette base de données a été realisée sous PostGreSQL. L'originalité principale de la nouvelle version de FLOW (v.3 et suivantes) est le schéma conceptuel (DBTNT) qui sépare les aspects nomenclaturaux objectifs de ceux taxonomiques, subjectifs (<I>Gallut C. et al., 2005a & 2005b, Final Workshop Species 2000, 14th Oct. 2005, Stockholm, Sueden</I>). Les pages d'exploration sont structurées en un réseau sémantique permettant un accès rapide et dynamique aux différents types de données.\r\n<br><br>\r\nLes outils logiciels informatiques qui ont été réalisés (ERC, DB2WEB, DBTNT, TaxaLife) ne sont pas spécifiques à FLOW, mais facilement adaptables à tout autre groupe taxonomique. On pourra consulter par exemple les bases de données sur les Phlébotomes (Diptera, Psychodidae : projet <A href='http://cipa.snv.jussieu.fr/'>CIPA</A>), celle des Cercopides (Hemiptera Cercopoidea : projet <A href='http://rameau.snv.jussieu.fr/cool/index.php'>COOL</A>) ou celle sur les Psylles (Hemiptera Psylloidea : projet <A href='http://rameau.snv.jussieu.fr/cgi-bin/psyllesexplorer.pl'>Psyl'list</A>).	This database has been realized with table-structured data, through PostGreSQL. The main originality of the new version of FLOW (v.3 and following) is that names and taxa in the conceptual schem (DBTNT) are treated separately to allow independent management of subjective taxonomic and objective nomenclatural aspects (<I>Gallut C. et al., 2005a & 2005b, Final Workshop Species 2000, 14th Oct. 2005, Stockholm, Sueden</I>). Pages are structured in a semantic network that permits an easy access to different information with a dynamic access to data.\r\n<br><br>\r\nComputerized tools (ERC, DB2WEB, DBTNT, TaxaLife) used in this project are not specific to FLOW but easily adaptable for any taxonomic group. For instance, similar databases already exist for sandflies (Diptera, Psychodidae: <A href='http://cipa.snv.jussieu.fr/'>CIPA</A> project), for froghoppers (Hemiptera Cercopoidea: <A href='http://rameau.snv.jussieu.fr/cool/index.php'>COOL</A> project) or jumping plant lice (Hemiptera Psylloidea: <A href='http://rameau.snv.jussieu.fr/cgi-bin/psyllesexplorer.pl'>Psyl'list</A> project).	Esta base de datos fue realizada bajo PostGreSQL. La originalidad principal de la nueva versión de FLOW (v.3 y siguiente) es el esquema conceptual (DBTNT) que separa los aspectos nomenclaturales objectivos y taxonómicos subjectivos  (<I>Gallut C. et al., 2005a & 2005b, Final Workshop Species 2000, 14th Oct. 2005, Stockholm, Sueden</I>).  Las páginas de exploración se estructuran en una red semántica que permite un acceso rápido y dinámico a los distintos tipos de datos. \r\n<br><br>\r\nOtros proyectos sobre otros grupos taxonómicos pueden usar este mismo systema (ERC, DB2WEB, DBTNT, TaxaLife) muy facilmente. Por ejemplo se puede consultar la base de datos sobre los flebotomos (Diptera, Psychodidae : projecto <A href='http://cipa.snv.jussieu.fr/'>CIPA</A>), la de los Cercopidos (Hemiptera Cercopoidea : projecto <A href='http://rameau.snv.jussieu.fr/cool/index.php'>COOL</A>) o la de los Psyllidos (Hemiptera Psylloidea : projecto <A href='http://rameau.snv.jussieu.fr/cgi-bin/psyllesexplorer.pl'>Psyl'list</A>).	Esta base de dados foi realizada com dados estruturados em tabela, através de PostGreSQL. \r\nA principal novidade da nova versão do FLOW (v.3 e seguintes) é que os nomes e taxa no esquema conceitual (DBTNT) são tratados separadamente para permitir o gerenciamento independente de aspectos taonômicos subjetivos e aspectos nomenclaturais objetivos (<I>Gallut C. et al., 2005a & 2005b, Final Workshop Species 2000, 14th Oct. 2005, Stockholm, Sueden</I>). As páginas estão estruturadas em uma rede semântica que permite acesso fácil a diferentes informações com acesso dinâmico aos dados. <br><br>\r\nAs ferramentas computacionais (ERC, DB2WEB, DBTNT, TaxaLife) usadas neste projeto não são específicas do FLOW, mas são facilmente adaptáveis  para qualquer grupo taxonômico. Por exemplo, bases de dados similares existem para Flebotomíneos (Diptera, Psychodidae: <A href='http://cipa.snv.jussieu.fr/'>CIPA</A> project), para cercopídeos (Hemiptera Cercopoidea: <A href='http://rameau.snv.jussieu.fr/cool/index.php'>COOL</A> project) e para psilídeos(Hemiptera Psylloidea: projeto <A href='http://rameau.snv.jussieu.fr/cgi-bin/psyllesexplorer.pl'>Psyl'list</A>).	This database has been realized with table-structured data, through PostGreSQL. The main originality of the new version of FLOW (v.3 and following) is that names and taxa in the conceptual schem (DBTNT) are treated separately to allow independent management of subjective taxonomic and objective nomenclatural aspects  (<I>Gallut C. et al., 2005a & 2005b, Final Workshop Species 2000, 14th Oct. 2005, Stockholm, Sueden</I>). Pages are structured in a semantic network that permits an easy access to different information with a dynamic access to data.\r\n<br><br>\r\nComputerized tools (ERC, DB2WEB, DBTNT, TaxaLife) used in this project are not specific to FLOW but easily adaptable for any taxonomic group. For instance, similar databases already exists for sandflies (Diptera, Psychodidae: <A href='http://cipa.snv.jussieu.fr/'>CIPA</A> project), for froghoppers (Hemiptera Cercopoidea: <A href='http://rameau.snv.jussieu.fr/cool/index.php'>COOL</A> project) or jumping plant lice (Hemiptera Psylloidea: <A href='http://rameau.snv.jussieu.fr/cgi-bin/psyllesexplorer.pl'>Psyl'list</A> project).	anta	2007-01-16	bourgoin	2014-02-05	This database has been realized with table-structured data, through PostGreSQL. The main originality of the new version of FLOW (v.3 and following) is that names and taxa in the conceptual schem (DBTNT) are treated separately to allow independent management of subjective taxonomic and objective nomenclatural aspects (<I>Gallut C. et al., 2005a & 2005b, Final Workshop Species 2000, 14th Oct. 2005, Stockholm, Sueden</I>). Pages are structured in a semantic network that permits an easy acce