intro_tessaratomidae	L'objectif de ce site est la mise en place d'un catalogue illustré des Tessaratomidae du Monde. Cela va prendre du temps, car l'auteur n'a pas encore vu l'ensemble des espèces de la famille, ni photographié tous les spécimens qu'il a vu, et de plus n'est pas encore sûr, pour quelques uns d'entre eux, de l'espèce à laquelle ils appartiennent. Le catalg évoluant avec les connaissances de son auteur, toute contribution (spécimens, images, identifiications) est la bienvenue.Toutes les photos, sauf mention expresse, sont la propriété de ce site. Celles de spécimens appartenant à des musées sont la propriété des musées correspondants. Elles peuvent être utilisées pour des publications à but scientifique ou illustratif, après autorisation du webmestre (qui pourra vous donner accès la résolution maximum des images).  La classification de la famille utilisée pour ce site découle de celle du catalogue des Tessaratomidae de Rolston, Aalbu, Murray & Rider (Rolston, L.H., Aalbu, R.L., Murray, M.J. & Rider, D.A. (1993). A catalog of the Tessaratomidae of the world. Papua New Guinea J. Agric., For. Fish 36: 36-108 [45] (catalogue)). Ils sont ici remerciés pour ce travail qui permet de trouver son chemin dans la jungle de cette famille... Je remercie aussi les musées et mes collègues qui ont permis la publication de photos de leurs spécimens. Meric également à tous ceux qui ont autorisé la publication de leur photos sur e site : Christophe Barthélémy, Les Day, Cathy Dzerefos, L C Goh, John Horstman, Michael Lo, Chan Yoke Meng, Geoff Monteith, David Rentz, Robert Whyte and Noel M. Young.	The objective of this site is to build an illustrated catalog of the World Tessaratomidae. It will take some time, as the author has not seen all species in this family, not yet photographed all the bugs he has seen, and more is not sure, for some of them, of the species they belong to. It will evolve with the knowledge of the author, so any contribution is welcome (bugs, pictures, identification).  All the pictures, unless explicitely mentioned, are the copyright of this site. The copyrights of picture of specimens from museums collections belong to the corresponding museums. They may be used in publication for scientific or illustration purposes, but only with the authorization of the webmaster of this site (which, by the way, will give you access to full resolution pictures).  The classification of the family used in this site derives from the catalog of Tessaratomidae of Rolston, Aalbu, Murray & Rider (Rolston, L.H., Aalbu, R.L., Murray, M.J. & Rider, D.A. (1993). A catalog of the Tessaratomidae of the world. Papua New Guinea J. Agric., For. Fish 36: 36-108 [45] (catalogue)). They must be thanked for this work which makes it possible to find one's way in the jungle of this family... Many thanks also to the museums and colleagues which allowed the publication of pictures of their specimens. A special thanks also to those who allowed me to put their pictures on this site, Christophe Barthélémy, Les Day, Cathy Dzerefos, L C Goh, John Horstman, Michael Lo, Chan Yoke Meng, Geoff Monteith, David Rentz, Robert Whyte and Noel M. Young.	The objective of this site is to build an illustrated catalog of the World Tessaratomidae. It will take some time, as the author has not seen all species in this family, not yet photographed all the bugs he has seen, and more is not sure, for some of them, of the species they belong to. It will evolve with the knowledge of the author, so any contribution is welcome (bugs, pictures, identification).  All the pictures, unless explicitely mentioned, are the copyright of this site. The copyrights of picture of specimens from museums collections belong to the corresponding museums. They may be used in publication for scientific or illustration purposes, but only with the authorization of the webmaster of this site (which, by the way, will give you access to full resolution pictures).  The classification of the family