inc_ethology	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p>Ces insectes sont phytophages et généralement liés à leur plante hôte. Cette dernière peut être un moyen de communiquer en étant un support pour la transmission de signaux vibratoires, ce qui a été observé jusqu’à présent chez certains Aphrophoridae (Ossiannilsson, 1949, Virant-Doberlet & Cokl, 2004).</p>\r\n<p>C’est sur cette même plante hôte que nous retrouvons les larves vivant dans des amas spumeux résultant du régime alimentaire de l’insecte et produits par des tubes de Malpighi spécialisés (Rakitov, 2002).</p>\r\n<img src="images/larveCercopismaculata.jpg" width="138" height="220" border="0">\r\n<img src="images/amas-spumeux.jpg" width="159" height="220" border="0">\r\n<img src="images/philaenus3.jpg" width="134" height="220" border="0">\r\n</div>	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p>These insects are phytophages and generally bound to their plant host. This last one can be a means to communicate by being a support for the transmission of vibratory signals. This was observed until now only for some Aphrophoridae (Ossiannilsson, 1949, Virant-Doberlet & Cokl, 2004).</p>\r\n<p>It is on the same plant host that we find larva living in a spumous froth resulting from the diet of the insect and produced by specialised Malpighi tubes (Rakitov, on 2002).</p>\r\n</div>	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p>Estos insectos son fit&oacute;fagos y generalmente atados a su planta hu&eacute;sped. Esta &uacute;ltima puede ser un medio de comunicar que es un soporte para la transmisi&oacute;n de se&ntilde;ales vibratorias, lo que ha sido observado hasta ahora en casa de cierto Aphrophoridae (Ossiannilsson, 1949, Virant-Doberlet y Cokl, 2004).</p>\r\n<p>Es sobre la planta hu&eacute;sped que reencontramos las larvas que viven en mont&oacute;n espumoso que resulta de la dieta del insecto y es producido por tubos de Malpighi especializado (Rakitov, 2002).</p>\r\n</div>	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p>Estes insetos são fitófagos e geralmente estão ligados às suas plantas hospedeiras. Estas últimas podem ser um meio para comunicação, sendo um suporte para a transmissão de sinais vibratórios. Até agora, isso foi observado apenas para alguns Aprhophoridae (Ossiannilsson, 1949, Virant-Doberlet & Cokl, 2004).</p>\r\n<p>\r\nÉ na mesma planta hospedeira que se encontram as larvas, que vivem em uma espuma resultante da dieta do inseto e produzida por túbulos de Malpighi especializados (Rakitov, on 2002).</p>\r\n</div>	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p>These insects are phytophages and generally bound to their plant host. This last one can be a means to communicate by being a support for the transmission of vibratory signals. This was observed until now only for some Aphrophoridae (Ossiannilsson, 1949, Virant-Doberlet & Cokl, 2004).</p>\r\n<p>It is on the same plant host that we find larva living in a spumous froth resulting from the diet of the insect and produced by specialised Malpighi tubes (Rakitov, on 2002).</p>\r\n</div>	soulier	2011-04-14	bourgoin	2014-02-05	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p>These insects are phytophages and generally bound to their plant host. This last one can be a means to communicate by being a support for the transmission of vibratory signals. This was observed until now only for some Aphrophoridae (Ossiannilsson, 1949, Virant-Doberlet & Cokl, 2004).</p>\r\n<p>It is on the same plant host that we find larva living in a spumous froth resulting from the diet of the insect and produced by specialised Malpighi tubes (Rakitov, on 2002).</p>\r\n</div>
