web_front_text	Strepsiptera database is a database on Strepsiptera parasitoïd group.\r\n<p>\r\nStrepsiptera (commonly known as twisted-winged parasites) is an order of\r\nholometabolous insects with twelve  families (one fossil genus undescribed\r\nas a family), making up about six hundred species so far with several\r\ncryptic species to be described. The 1st instar larvae and the short-lived\r\nadult males are the only free-living stages (except in the family\r\nMengenillidae). The larval stages and the neotenic females  are\r\nendoparasites. The hosts include insects such as bees, wasps, leafhoppers,\r\nsilverfish, cockroaches, grasshoppers, mantids, crickets and fruitflies.\r\n	Strepsiptera database is a database on Strepsiptera parasitoïd group.\r\n<p>\r\nStrepsiptera (commonly known as twisted-winged parasites) is an order of\r\nholometabolous insects with twelve  families (one fossil genus undescribed\r\nas a family), making up about six hundred species so far with several\r\ncryptic species to be described. The 1st instar larvae and the short-lived\r\nadult males are the only free-living stages (except in the family\r\nMengenillidae). The larval stages and the neotenic females  are\r\nendoparasites. The hosts include insects such as bees, wasps, leafhoppers,\r\nsilverfish, cockroaches, grasshoppers, mantids, crickets and fruitflies.\r\n	La base de datos Strepsiptera es una base de datos sobre el grupo de parasitóides Strepsiptera.\r\n<p>\r\nLos Strepsiptera (conocidos en inglés como twisted-winged parasites) son un orden de insectos holometábolos con doce famílias (un fóssil no descrito como família), totalizando unas 600 especies hasta hoy, con varias especies crípticas por describir. El larva de primer instar y los adultos de vida corta son los únicos estágios de vida libre (excepto en la família Mengenillidae). Los estágios larvales y las hembras neotenicas son endoparasitos. Los huéspedes incluyen insectos tales como abejas, avispas, cicadélidos, tisanuros, cucarachas, mantis, grillos y moscas de las frutas. \r\n\r\n	Strepsiptera é uma base de dados sobre o grupo de parasitóides Strepsiptera.\r\n<p>\r\nOs Strepsiptera (conhecidos em inglês como twisted-winged parasites) são uma ordem de insetos holometábolos com doze famílias (um gênero fóssil não descrito como família), totalizando cerca de 600 espécies até agora, com várias espécies crípticas a serem descritas. As larvas de 1° ínstar e os adultos machos de vida curta são os únicos estágios de vida livre (exceto na família Mengenillidae). Os estágios larvais e as fêmeas neotênicas são endoparasitas. Os hospedeiros incluem insetos como abelhas, vespas, cicadelídeos, traças (Thysanura), baratas, gafanhotos, louva-a-deus, grilos e moscas das frutas.	Strepsiptera database is a database on Strepsiptera parasitoïd group.\r\n<p>\r\nStrepsiptera (commonly known as twisted-winged parasites) is an order of\r\nholometabolous insects with twelve  families (one fossil genus undescribed\r\nas a family), making up about six hundred species so far with several\r\ncryptic species to be described. The 1st instar larvae and the short-lived\r\nadult males are the only free-living stages (except in the family\r\nMengenillidae). The larval stages and the neotenic females  are\r\nendoparasites. The hosts include insects such as bees, wasps, leafhoppers,\r\nsilverfish, cockroaches, grasshoppers, mantids, crickets and fruitflies.\r\n	bourgoin	2011-05-29	bourgoin	2014-02-06	Strepsiptera database is a database on Strepsiptera parasitoïd group.\r\n<p>\r\nStrepsiptera (commonly known as twisted-winged parasites) is an order of\r\nholometabolous insects with twelve  families (one fossil genus undescribed\r\nas a family), making up about six hundred species so far with several\r\ncryptic species to be described. The 1st instar larvae and the short-lived\r\nadult males are the only free-living stages (except in the family\r\nMengenillidae). The larval stages and the neotenic females  are\r\nendo