mbb_intro	The MBB – Moss Bug Base is a taxonomic database of extant and fossil taxa of Coleorrhyncha. It contains information on taxonomy (accepted names and synonyms), nomenclature, bibliography and distribution as basis for further studies on these insects. It is intended to add information on host relationships for extant taxa and on stratigraphy for fossil taxa in future releases.	The MBB – Moss Bug Base is a taxonomic database of extant and fossil taxa of Coleorrhyncha. It contains information on taxonomy (accepted names and synonyms), nomenclature, bibliography and distribution as basis for further studies on these insects. It is intended to add information on host relationships for extant taxa and on stratigraphy for fossil taxa in future releases.	La MBB – Moss Bug Base es una base de datos taxonómica de taxa vivientes y fossiles de Coleorrhynca. Contiene información sobre la taxonomía (nombres aceptados y sininímias), nomenclatura, bibliografia y distribución como base para el estudio de estos insectos. Tenemos el intento de añadir información sobre relaciones con hospederos para taxa vivientes y sobre estratigrafía para taxa fosiles en versiones futuras.	A MBB- Moss Bug Base é uma base de dados taxonômica dos taxa viventes e fósseis de Coleorrhyncha. Contém informação taxonômica (nomes aceitos e sinonímias), nomenclatural, bibliográfica e de distribuição como base para estudos posteriores sobre estes insetos. Pretendemos adicionar informações sobre as relações com o hospedeiro para os taxa viventes e sobre estratigrafia para os taxa fósseis em versões futuras.	The MBB – Moss Bug Base is a taxonomic database of extant and fossil taxa of Coleorrhyncha. It contains information on taxonomy (accepted names and synonyms), nomenclature, bibliography and distribution as basis for further studies on these insects. It is intended to add information on host relationships for extant taxa and on stratigraphy for fossil taxa in future releases.	sheng	2009-10-08	bourgoin