dbtnt_standards	<SPAN STYLE='font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.2em;'>Standards et thesaurus utilisés pour FLOW</SPAN>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<B>Introduction</B>\r\n<br><br>\r\nL'emploi de standards et de thesaurus reconnus est essentiel pour pouvoir partager les données dans l'espace digital où se développe désormais la recherche en biodiversité. Ils sont nombreux et ils s'appliquent à tous les niveaux d'échange de l'information, qu'ils soient techniques ou conceptuels (comme le statut d'un taxon). Leur publication par les bases de données biologiques doit être encouragée pour accélérer leur reconnaissance dans et au-delà de la communauté du domaine de la biodiversité.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\nLes bases de données de la famille DBTNT - comme FLOW - suivent les \r\n<A href='//http://vocabularies.gbif.org/'>standards du GBIF</A>, le Système Mondial d'Information sur la Biodiversité, et du <A href='http://vocabularies.gbif.org/biblio/Markus-D%C3%B6ring/2009'>\r\nDarwin Core</A>, publiés par Markus Döring, le 08/03/2009. Ratifié par le <A href='http://www.tdwg.org/'>TDWG</A>, le <A href='http://www.tdwg.org/activities/darwincore/'>Darwin Core</A> (DwC) décrit les normes minimales de recherche et d'extraction dans des bases de données de collections d'histoire naturelle et d'observations. Le Darwin Core et ses extensions sont basés sur les standards <A href='http://wiki.tdwg.org/ABCD/'>ABCD</A> (Access to Biological Collection Data) et internationaux (e.g. ISO et TDWG).\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<B>1. Statut taxonomique</B>\r\n<br>Compatible avec les recommandations du <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w'>Darwin Core Vocabularies </A>pour le statut taxonomique.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>2. Nomenclatural code</B><br>\r\nLa nomenclature de FLOW respecte le code de l' <A href='http://www.iczn.org/'>ICZN</A> (International Code of Zoological Nomenclature).\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>3. Statut de rang taxonomique</B><br>\r\nSuit les recommandations du <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=14'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> pour le statut de rang taxonomique.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>4. Status d'occurrence </B><br>\r\nQuand indiqué, suit les recommandations du <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=3'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> pour les occurences.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>5. Statuts  d'établissement de l'espèce</B><br>\r\nQuand indiqué, suit les recommandations de statut du <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=4'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A>.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>6. Statut IUCN</B><br>\r\nDonnées non encore présentées dans la base FLOW. Elles suivront les catégories publiées par la liste rouge de l'<A href='http://www.iucnredlist.org/'>IUCN</A> comme le recommande le <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=8'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A>.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>7. Statut IUCN du type d'habitat</B><br>\r\nDonnées non encore présentées dans la base FLOW. Elles suivront les types d'habitat proposés par le <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=11)'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A>.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>8. Standards de répartition </B><br>\r\nFLOW suit les standards du <A href='http://www.tdwg.org/standards/109/'>TDWG</A> dont le 'World Geographical Scheme for Recording Plant Distributions niveaux 3 et 4 pour le champ pays. Il n'y a pas de  standard disponible pour les régions  biogéographiques. Dans certains cas un niveau supplémentaire est introduit (pour tenir compte d'une répartion insulaire plus précise par exemple). Les cartes de répartitions sont générées par les services <A 'href= http://dev.e-taxonomy.eu/trac/wiki/MapRestServiceApi'>Map REST d'EDIT</A>. \r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>9. Echelle des temps géologiques</B><br>\r\nSuit le standard 2017 (dates et nomenclature) établi par la Commission Internationale de Stratigraphie (ICSL, <A href='http://www.stratigraphy.org/index.php/ics-chart-timescale'>International Commission on Stratigraphy</A>).\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>10. Classification botanique des plantes-hôtes</B><br>\r\nPour les noms d'espèces botaniques valides, FLOW ne fournit pas nécessairement le nom de cité en référence mais celui retenu par la base <A href='http://www.tropicos.org/Home.aspx'>TROPICOS </A> (Missouri Botanical Garden, 4344 Shaw Boulevard, Saint Louis, Missouri 63110, USA) pour toute information nomenclaturale, bibliographique ou de classification. Si l'information n'est pas disponible dans TROPICOS (e.g. pas de nom valide), FLOW se réfère alors au <A href='http://www.catalogueoflife.org/annual-checklist/search.php'>Catalogue of Life Annual checklist</A> de Species 2000. En dernier recours, le nom saisi sera celui publié par la référence citée.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>11. Classification supra-familiale des Hemiptera</B><br>\r\nFLOW suit la base de données <A href='http://flow.snv.jussieu.fr/cgi-bin/classif.pl'>HemClas</A>, mise à jour et reprise de Bourgoin Th., J. Swzedo & F. Lefèbvre, 2004 <i>(About Hemiptera phylogeny and Classification, :11-36. In: Fossil Planthoppers (Hemiptera: Fulgoromorpha) of the world. An annotated catalogue with notes on Hemiptera classification. Swzedo, J., Th. Bourgoin & F. Lefèbvre. J. Swzedo edt., Warsaw 2004, 199 pp + 8 pl)</i>. HemClas est disponible dans HemBase, le groupe de bases de données du MNHN-Paris sur les Hémiptères.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>12. Espèces et 'Peer-review'</B><br>\r\nFLOW est basé sur les données des catalogues de Metcalf pour les Fulgoromorpha, mises à jour depuis. De même pour les données de publication également disponibles en ligne sur le site <A href='http://metcalf.lib.ncsu.edu/metcalf/?refine=true'>Dr Metcalf</A>.\r\nFLOW a été 'peer-reviewé' (2007, 2012) par Species 2000 et retenu comme le fournisseur de données systématiques pour les Hemiptera Fulgoromorpha dans 'Catalogue of Life'. \r\nCe dernier sert de réference taxonomique (ou de standard pour les espèces valides!) pour diverses initiatives mondiales comme le GBIF, EoL (Encyplopedy of Life), GenBank, CBoL (Consortium for the Barcode of Life), … \r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>13. Codes des Collections</B><br>\r\nLorsqu'elles sont mentionnées, les collections où sont déposés les types sont codées suivant l'index <A href='http://www.biodiversitycollectionsindex.org/static/index.html'>BCI</A> (Biodiversity Collection Index) qui permet de distinguer chaque collection sans ambiguité.Les données sont celles citées dans les articles originaux ou celles mises à jour par des articles plus récents.	<SPAN STYLE='font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.2em;'>General standards and thesaurus used in FLOW</SPAN>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<B>Introduction</B>\r\n<br><br>\r\nTechnical standards and accepted thesaurus are fundamental to exchange data in the new digital space in which biodiversity research is now evolving. They are numerous and concern all levels of information from IT perspectives to elaborated knowledge concept (and first of all in the field of biodiversity, the status of a taxon specially). Their publication by each biodiversity database should be recommanded in order to accelerate their use and recognition within and outside the biodiversity community.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\nDBTNT family databases - as FLOW - follow the <A href='http://vocabularies.gbif.org/'>GBIF Vocabularies </A> and the <A href='http://vocabularies.gbif.org/biblio/Markus-D%C3%B6ring/2009'>\r\nDarwin Core Vocabularies</A> (published by Markus Döring, 08/03/2009). The <A href='http://www.tdwg.org/activities/darwincore/'>Darwin Core</A> (DwC) has been ratifief and is the recommended standard to be used by the <A href='http://www.tdwg.org/'>TDWG</A> (Biodiversity Information Standards). It describes the minimum set of standards for search and retrieval of natural history collections and observation databases. The Darwin Core and its extensions are based on the <A href='http://wiki.tdwg.org/ABCD/'>ABCD</A> (Access to Biological Collection Data) standards and on internationally recognized standards (e.g. ISO and TDWG). \r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<B>1.Taxonomic status</B>\r\n<br>Compatible with the <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w'>Darwin Core Vocabularies </A> for taxonomic status.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<B>2. Nomenclatural code</B><br>\r\nFollows <A href='http://www.iczn.org/'>ICZN</A> code (International Code of Zoological Nomenclature).\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>3. Taxon rank status</B><br>\r\nFollows the <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=14'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> for the taxon rank.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>4. Occurrence status</B><br>\r\nWhen stated it follows the <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=3'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> for the occurrence status.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>5. Establisment Means status</B><br>\r\nWhen stated it follows the <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=4'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> for the establishment means status.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>6. IUCN threat status</B><br>\r\nNot yet registered in DBTNT family databases. When it will be, it will follow the <A href='http://www.iucnredlist.org/'>IUCN red list of Threatened Species</A> categories as recommended by the <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=8'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A>.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>7. IUCN Habitat types</B><br>\r\nNot yet registered in DBTNT family databases. When it will be, it will follows the types proposed by the <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=11)'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> for IUCN habitats types.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>8. Distribution standards</B><br>\r\nFLOW follows the <A href='http://www.tdwg.org/standards/109/'>TDWG</A> standard 'World Geographical Scheme for Recording Plant Distributions levels 3 and 4 that documents species distribution at the countries level. There is no available standard for biogeographical regions. In some cases, level 4 data has been subdivided in a lower level (to take into account island distribution for instance). Distribution maps are generated using the <A 'href= http://dev.e-taxonomy.eu/trac/wiki/MapRestServiceApi'>EDIT Map REST</A> services.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>9. Geological time scale</B><br>\r\nFollows the 2017 standard (dates and nomenclature) of the \r\n<A href='http://www.stratigraphy.org/index.php/ics-chart-timescale'>International Commission on Stratigraphy</A>.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>10. Host-plants Taxonomy and botanical classification</B><br>\r\nFor accepted names of botanical species, FLOW do not necessarily follows the taxonomic name provided with the linked reference but it refers to the <A href='http://www.tropicos.org/Home.aspx'>TROPICOS </A> database for all of the nomenclatural, bibliographic, and plant classification as provided by the Missouri Botanical Garden, 4344 Shaw Boulevard, Saint Louis, Missouri 63110, USA. If the taxonomic status names is not provided by TROPICOS (e.g. no accepted name), FLOW follows the <A href='http://www.catalogueoflife.org/annual-checklist/search.php'>Species 2000 Catalogue of Life annual checklist</A>. Ultimately, if no match, the name registered will be the one provided by the reference cited.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>11. Hemiptera supra familial classification</B><br>\r\nFLOW follows <A href='http://flow.snv.jussieu.fr/cgi-bin/classif.pl'>HemClas</A>, the suprafamilal Hemiptera classification updated from <i>(Bourgoin Th., J. Swzedo & F. Lefèbvre, 2004. About Hemiptera phylogeny and Classification, :11-36. In: Fossil Planthoppers (Hemiptera: Fulgoromorpha) of the world. An annotated catalogue with notes on Hemiptera classification. Swzedo, J., Th. Bourgoin & F. Lefèbvre. J. Swzedo edt., Warsaw 2004, 199 pp + 8 pl)</i>. HemClas is available in HemBase, the MNHN-Paris Hemiptera database package.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>12. Species and Peer-review</B><br>\r\nFLOW is based on the Metcalf catalogues for the Fulgoromorpha which have been updated. Resources for litterature follows basically these catalogues also available at the <A href='http://metcalf.lib.ncsu.edu/metcalf/?refine=true'>Dr Metcalf</A> website.\r\nFLOW has been peer reviewed (2007, 2012) by the Species 2000 and ITIS Consortium and accepted as provider for the planthoppers (Hemiptera, Fulgoromorpha) referenced names and taxa in the Catologue of Life. \r\nThe Catalogue of Life serves as the taxonomic backbone (or the standard for valid species!) for various global initiatives as the GBIF, EoL (Encyplopedy of Life), GenBank, CBoL (Consortium for the Barcode of Life), … \r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>13. Collection coding</B><br>\r\nDepositories of type specimen follows the <A href='http://www.biodiversitycollectionsindex.org/static/index.html'>BCI index</A> (Biodiversity Collection Index) which unambiguously references collections. Data are collected from the original paper or, when available, from more updated referenced sources.	<SPAN STYLE='font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.2em;'>Estándares generales y thesaurus usados en FLOW </SPAN>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<B>Introducción</B>\r\n<br><br>\r\nEstándares técnicos y thesaurus reconocidos son fundamentales al intercambio de datos en los nuevos espacios digitales en los cuales la investigación en biodiversidad evolue ahora. Ellos son numerosos y dicen respeto a todos los niveles de información, de perspectivas de TI a conceptos elaborados del contenido ( y primero de todo en el campo de la biodiversidad, el status de un taxon especialmente). La publicación de estos estándares en cada base de datos de biodiversidade es recomendable, en en sentido de acelerar su uso y reconocimiento dentro y fuera de la comunidad de biodiversidad. \r\n<br>\r\nLas bases de datos de la família DBTNT- como FLOW – siguen el <A href='http://vocabularies.gbif.org/'>GBIF Vocabularies </A> bien como el <A href='http://vocabularies.gbif.org/biblio/Markus-D%C3%B6ring/2009'>\r\nDarwin Core Vocabularies</A> (published by Markus Döring, 08/03/2009). El <A href='http://www.tdwg.org/activities/darwincore/'>Darwin Core</A> (DwC) ha sido ratificado y es el estándar recomendado pela <A href='http://www.tdwg.org/'>TDWG</A> (Biodiversity Information Standards). Él describe el conjunto mínimo de estándares de busqueda y extracción en bases de datos de história natural y de observación. El Darwin Core y sus extensiones se basan en los padrones del <A href='http://wiki.tdwg.org/ABCD/'>ABCD</A> (Access to Biological Collection Data) y en estándares internacionalmente reconocidos (como ISO and TDWG). \r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<B>1.Status taxonómico</B>\r\n<br>Compatible con el <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w'>Darwin Core Vocabularies </A> para status taxonómico.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<B>2. Código Nomenclatural </B><br>\r\nSigue el código de la <A href='http://www.iczn.org/'>ICZN</A> (International Code of Zoological Nomenclature).\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>3. Status taxonómico jerárquico </B><br>\r\nSigue el <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=14'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> para jerarquía taxonómica.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>4.Status de la ocurrencia</B><br>\r\nCuándo segnalado, sigue el <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=3'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> para el status de ocurrencia.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>5. Status de establecimiento de la especie</B><br>\r\nCuándo indicado, sigue el <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=4'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> para el status de establecimiento de especie.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>6. Status de amenaza en IUCN</B><br>\r\nAún no registrado en bases de datos de la família DBTNT. Cuándo lo sea, seguirá las categorías de la <A href='http://www.iucnredlist.org/'>lista roja de especies amenazadas de IUCN </A>, como recomendado por  el <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=8'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A>.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>7. Tipos de habitat por la IUCN </B><br>\r\nAún no registrado en bases de datos de la família DBTNT. Cuándo lo sea, seguirá los tipos propuestos por el <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=11)'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> para los tipos de habitat por la IUCN.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>8. Patrones de distribución </B><br>\r\nFLOW sigue el estándar <A href='http://www.tdwg.org/standards/109/'>TDWG</A> 'World Geographical Scheme for Recording Plant Distributions niveles 3 y 4, aue documenta la distribución de las especies en nivel de país. No hay un estándar para regiones biogeográficas. En algunos casos, un nivel adicional ha sido puesto (para dar cuenta de distribuciones insulares, por ejemplo). Mapas de distribución son generados usando los servicios de <A 'href= http://dev.e-taxonomy.eu/trac/wiki/MapRestServiceApi'>EDIT Map REST</A>\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>9. Escala de tiempo geológico</B><br>\r\nSigue el estándar 2017 (datas y nomenclatura) de la \r\n<A href='http://www.stratigraphy.org/index.php/ics-chart-timescale'>International Commission on Stratigraphy</A>.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>10. Taxonomía de las plantas -huésped </B><br>\r\nPara los nombres acetos de espánicas, FLOW no necesariamente sigue el nombre taxonómico fornecido por la referéncia asociada, pero se refiere a la base de datos <A href='http://www.tropicos.org/Home.aspx'>TROPICOS </A>  para toda la nomenclatura, bibliografía y clasificación botánica como provida por el Missouri Botanical Garden, 4344 Shaw Boulevard, Saint Louis, Missouri 63110, USA. Si la información no se encontra disponible en TROPICOS (ejemplo, nombre non aceptado), FLOW sigue el <A href='http://www.catalogueoflife.org/annual-checklist/search.php'>Species 2000 Catalogue of Life annual checklist</A>. Finalmente, si no hay combinación, el nombre registrado será el provido por la referéncia citada.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>11. Classificación supra-familiar de los Hemiptera\r\n</B><br>\r\nFLOW sigue <A href='http://flow.snv.jussieu.fr/cgi-bin/classif.pl'>HemClas</A>, la clasificación supra-familiar de los Hemiptera atualizada de <i>(Bourgoin Th., J. Swzedo & F. Lefèbvre, 2004. About Hemiptera phylogeny and Classification, :11-36. In: Fossil Planthoppers (Hemiptera: Fulgoromorpha) of the world. An annotated catalogue with notes on Hemiptera classification. Swzedo, J., Th. Bourgoin & F. Lefèbvre. J. Swzedo edt., Warsaw 2004, 199 pp + 8 pl)</i>. HemClas está disponible en la HemBase, el paquete de base de datos de Hemiptera del MNHN-Paris.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>12. Espécies y Peer-review</B><br>\r\nFLOW se basa en los catálogos Metcalf para los Fulgoromorpha, los cuales han sido actualizados. Lo mismo para los datos de publicación, igualmente disponibles en la página de<A href='http://metcalf.lib.ncsu.edu/metcalf/?refine=true'>Dr Metcalf</A>.\r\nFLOW ha sido peer reviewed (2007, 2012) por el Species 2000 y ITIS Consortium y acepto como provedor de nombres y taxa referenciados para los fulgoromorfos (Hemiptera, Fulgoromorpha) en el Catologue of Life. \r\nEl Catalogue of Life sirve como esaueleto taxonómico (o el estándar para especies válidas!) para muchas iniciativas globales, como el GBIF, EoL (Encyplopedy of Life), GenBank, CBoL (Consortium for the Barcode of Life), … \r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>13. Códigos de las colecciones </B><br>\r\nDepositórios de especímenes-tipo siguen el <A href='http://www.biodiversitycollectionsindex.org/static/index.html'>BCI index</A> (Biodiversity Collection Index) que referencia colecciones sin ambiguidad. Los datos son colectados del paper original, o, cuando disponibles, de fontes de datos referenciadas más actualizadas. \r\n	<SPAN STYLE='font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.2em;'>Padrões gerais e Thesaurus usados no FLOW</SPAN>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<B>Introdução</B>\r\n<br><br>\r\nPadrões técnicos e thesaurus reconhecidos são fundamentais para o compartilhamento de dados nos novos espaços digitais em que a pesquisa em biodiversidade está se desenvolvendo. Eles são muitos e dizem respeito a todos os níveis de informação, da perspectiva da TI até conceitos elaborados de conteúdo (e, antes de tudo, no campo da biodiversidade, o conceito de taxon, especialmente). Sua publicação por cada base de dados em biodiversidade é altamente recomendável, com o intuito de acelerar seu uso e reconhecimento dentro e fora da comunidade de biodiversidade. \r\n<br>\r\n<br>As bases de dados do tipo DBTNT - como a FLOW – seguem os <A href='http://vocabularies.gbif.org/'>padrões do GBIF</A> e o<A href='http://vocabularies.gbif.org/biblio/Markus-D%C3%B6ring/2009'>\r\nDarwin Core Vocabularies</A> (publicado por Markus Döring, 08/03/2009). Ratificado pela <A href='http://www.tdwg.org/'>TDWG</A>, o <A href='http://www.tdwg.org/activities/darwincore/'>Darwin Core</A> (DwC) descreve as normas mínimas de busca e extração nas bases de dados de coleções de história natural e de observação. O Darwin Core e suas extensões são feitos com base nos padrões <A href='http://wiki.tdwg.org/ABCD/'>ABCD</A> (Access to Biological Collection Data) e em padrões reconhecidos internacionalmente, como ISO e TDWG. \r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<B>1. Status taxonômico</B>\r\n<br>Compatível com o <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w'>Darwin Core Vocabularies </A> para status taxonômico.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<B>2. Códigos nomenclaturais </B><br>\r\nSeguimos o código da <A href='http://www.iczn.org/'>ICZN</A>  (International Code of Zoological Nomenclature).\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>3. Status taxonômico hierárquico</B><br>\r\nSeguimos o <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=14'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> para a hierarquia taxonômica.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>4. Status de ocorrência</B><br>\r\nQuando indicado, seguimos as recomendações do <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=3'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> para dados de ocorrência.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>5. Status de estabelecimento da espécie</B><br>\r\nQuando indicado, seguimos as recomendações do <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=4'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> para o status de estabelecimento da espécie.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>6. Status de ameaça segundo a IUCN </B><br>\r\nAinda não registrado nas bases de dados do tipo DBTNT.  Quando registrado , seguirá as categorias da <A href='http://www.iucnredlist.org/'>lista vermelha de espécies ameaçadas da IUCN </A>, como recomendado pelo <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=8'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A>.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>7. Tipos de habitats segundo a IUCN</B><br>\r\nAinda não registrado nas bases de dados do tipo DBTNT. Quando registrado, seguirá os tipos propostos pelo <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=11)'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A>.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>8. Padrões de distribuição</B><br>\r\nO FLOW segue o padrão da <A href='http://www.tdwg.org/standards/109/'>TDWG</A> 'World Geographical Scheme for Recording Plant Distributions, niveis 3 e 4’, que documenta a distribuição das espécies ao nível de país. Não há um padrão disponível para regiões biogeográficas. Em alguns casos, um nível adicional foi introduzido (para dar conta de distribuições insulares mais precisas, por exemplo). Mapas de distribuição são gerados usando os serviços do <A 'href= http://dev.e-taxonomy.eu/trac/wiki/MapRestServiceApi'>EDIT Map REST</A>.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>9. Escala de tempo geológico</B><br>\r\nSeguimos os padrões 2017 (datas e nomenclatura) da\r\n<A href='http://www.stratigraphy.org/index.php/ics-chart-timescale'>International Commission on Stratigraphy</A>.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>10. Classificação botânica e taxonomia das plantas hospedeiras </B><br>\r\nPara os nomes aceitos de espécies de plantas, o FLOW não necessariamente segue o nome taxonômico provido pela referência utilizada, se referindo, no entanto à base de dados <A href='http://www.tropicos.org/Home.aspx'>TROPICOS </A> para todos os aspectos nomenclaturais, bibliográficos e de classificação de plantas, como fornecidos pelo Missouri Botanical Garden, 4344 Shaw Boulevard, Saint Louis, Missouri 63110, USA. Se o status taxonômico do nome não se encontra no TROPICOS (por exemplo, nome não aceito), o FLOW segue o \r\n<A href='http://www.catalogueoflife.org/annual-checklist/search.php'>Species 2000 Catalogue of Life annual checklist</A>. \r\nFinalmente, se não houver correspondência, o nome registrado será aquele fornecido pela referência citada.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>11. Classificação supra-familiar dos Hemiptera </B><br>\r\nO FLOW segue a <A href='http://flow.snv.jussieu.fr/cgi-bin/classif.pl'>HemClas</A>, a classificação suprafamiliar de Hemiptera atualizada de <i>(Bourgoin Th., J. Swzedo & F. Lefèbvre, 2004. About Hemiptera phylogeny and Classification, :11-36. In: Fossil Planthoppers (Hemiptera: Fulgoromorpha) of the world. An annotated catalogue with notes on Hemiptera classification. Swzedo, J., Th. Bourgoin & F. Lefèbvre. J. Swzedo edt., Warsaw 2004, 199 pp + 8 pl)</i>. A HemClas encontra-se disponível na HemBase, o pacote da base de dados de Hemiptera do MNHN-Paris.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>12. Espécies e revisão por pares</B><br>\r\nO FLOW se baseia nos catálogos Metcalf para os Fulgoromorpha, que tem sido atualizados. O mesmo para dados de publicação, também disponíveis na página do <A href='http://metcalf.lib.ncsu.edu/metcalf/?refine=true'>Dr Metcalf</A>.\r\nO FLOW foi revisado por pares (2007, 2012) pelo Species 2000 e pelo ITIS Consortium e aceito como fornecedor de nomes e taxa referenciados para Hemiptera, Fulgoromorpha no Catologue of Life. \r\nO Catalogue of Life funciona como um esqueleto taxonômico (ou o padrão para espécies válidas!) para várias iniciativas mundiais, como o GBIF, EoL (Encyplopedy of Life), GenBank, CBoL (Consortium for the Barcode of Life), entre outras. \r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>13. Códigos das coleções</B><br>\r\nDepositórios de espécimes-tipo seguem o <A href='http://www.biodiversitycollectionsindex.org/static/index.html'>BCI index</A> (Biodiversity Collection Index) que permite distinguir cada coleção sem ambiguidade. Os dados são coletados nos artigos originais ou, quando disponíveis, de fontes referenciadas mais atualizadas. \r\n	<SPAN STYLE='font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.2em;'>General standards and thesaurus used in FLOW</SPAN>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<B>Introduction</B>\r\n<br><br>\r\nTechnical standards and accepted thesaurus are fundamental to exchange data in the new digital space in which biodiversity research is now evolving. They are numerous and concern all levels of information from IT perspectives to elaborated knowledge concept (and first of all in the field of biodiversity, the status of a taxon specially). Their publication by each biodiversity database should be recommanded in order to accelerate their use and recognition within and outside the biodiversity community.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\nDBTNT family databases - as FLOW - follow the <A href='http://vocabularies.gbif.org/'>GBIF Vocabularies </A> and the <A href='http://vocabularies.gbif.org/biblio/Markus-D%C3%B6ring/2009'>\r\nDarwin Core Vocabularies</A> (published by Markus Döring, 08/03/2009). The <A href='http://www.tdwg.org/activities/darwincore/'>Darwin Core</A> (DwC) has been ratifief and is the recommended standard to be used by the <A href='http://www.tdwg.org/'>TDWG</A> (Biodiversity Information Standards). It describes the minimum set of standards for search and retrieval of natural history collections and observation databases. The Darwin Core and its extensions are based on the <A href='http://wiki.tdwg.org/ABCD/'>ABCD</A> (Access to Biological Collection Data) standards and on internationally recognized standards (e.g. ISO and TDWG). \r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<B>1.Taxonomic status</B>\r\n<br>Compatible with the <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w'>Darwin Core Vocabularies </A> for taxonomic status.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<B>2. Nomenclatural code</B><br>\r\nFollows <A href='http://www.iczn.org/'>ICZN</A> code (International Code of Zoological Nomenclature).\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>3. Taxon rank status</B><br>\r\nFollows the <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=14'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> for the taxon rank.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>4. Occurrence status</B><br>\r\nWhen stated it follows the <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=3'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> for the occurrence status.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>5. Establisment Means status</B><br>\r\nWhen stated it follows the <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=4'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> for the establishment means status.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>6. IUCN threat status</B><br>\r\nNot yet registered in DBTNT family databases. When it will be, it will follow the <A href='http://www.iucnredlist.org/'>IUCN red list of Threatened Species</A> categories as recommended by the <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=8'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A>.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>7. IUCN Habitat types</B><br>\r\nNot yet registered in DBTNT family databases. When it will be, it will follows the types proposed by the <A href='http://spreadsheets.google.com/pub?key=tVs-UWMXnkD3slwIE8T336w&gid=11)'>Darwin Core Vocabularies</A> for IUCN habitats types.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>8. Distribution standards</B><br>\r\nFLOW follows the <A href='http://www.tdwg.org/standards/109/'>TDWG</A> standard 'World Geographical Scheme for Recording Plant Distributions levels 3 and 4 that documents species distribution at the countries level. There is no available standard for biogeographical regions. In some cases, level 4 data has been subdivided in a lower level (to take into account island distribution for instance). Distribution maps are generated using the <A 'href= http://dev.e-taxonomy.eu/trac/wiki/MapRestServiceApi'>EDIT Map REST</A> services.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>9. Geological time scale</B><br>\r\nFollows the 2017 standard (dates and nomenclature) of the \r\n<A href='http://www.stratigraphy.org/index.php/ics-chart-timescale'>International Commission on Stratigraphy</A>.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>10. Host-plants Taxonomy and botanical classification</B><br>\r\nFor accepted names of botanical species, FLOW do not necessarily follows the taxonomic name provided with the linked reference but it refers to the <A href='http://www.tropicos.org/Home.aspx'>TROPICOS </A> database for all of the nomenclatural, bibliographic, and plant classification as provided by the Missouri Botanical Garden, 4344 Shaw Boulevard, Saint Louis, Missouri 63110, USA. If the taxonomic status names is not provided by TROPICOS (e.g. no accepted name), FLOW follows the <A href='http://www.catalogueoflife.org/annual-checklist/search.php'>Species 2000 Catalogue of Life annual checklist</A>. Ultimately, if no match, the name registered will be the one provided by the reference cited.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>11. Hemiptera supra familial classification</B><br>\r\nFLOW follows <A href='http://flow.snv.jussieu.fr/cgi-bin/classif.pl'>HemClas</A>, the suprafamilal Hemiptera classification updated from <i>(Bourgoin Th., J. Swzedo & F. Lefèbvre, 2004. About Hemiptera phylogeny and Classification, :11-36. In: Fossil Planthoppers (Hemiptera: Fulgoromorpha) of the world. An annotated catalogue with notes on Hemiptera classification. Swzedo, J., Th. Bourgoin & F. Lefèbvre. J. Swzedo edt., Warsaw 2004, 199 pp + 8 pl)</i>. HemClas is available in HemBase, the MNHN-Paris Hemiptera database package.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>12. Species and Peer-review</B><br>\r\nFLOW is based on the Metcalf catalogues for the Fulgoromorpha which have been updated. Resources for litterature follows basically these catalogues also available at the <A href='http://metcalf.lib.ncsu.edu/metcalf/?refine=true'>Dr Metcalf</A> website.\r\nFLOW has been peer reviewed (2007, 2012) by the Species 2000 and ITIS Consortium and accepted as provider for the planthoppers (Hemiptera, Fulgoromorpha) referenced names and taxa in the Catologue of Life. \r\nThe Catalogue of Life serves as the taxonomic backbone (or the standard for valid species!) for various global initiatives as the GBIF, EoL (Encyplopedy of Life), GenBank, CBoL (Consortium for the Barcode of Life), … \r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<B>13. Collection coding</B><br>\r\nDepositories of type specimen follows the <A href='http://www.biodiversitycollectionsindex.org/static/index.html'>BCI index</A> (Biodiversity Collection Index) which unambiguously references collections. Data are collected from the original paper or, when available, from more updated referenced sources.	guest	2009-10-18	guest	2018-01-19	<SPAN STYLE='font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.2em;'>General standards and thesaurus used in FLOW</SPAN>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<B>Introduction</B>\r\n<br><br>\r\nTechnical standards and accepted thesaurus are fundamental to exchange data in the new digital space in which biodiversity research is now evolving. They are numerous and concern all levels of information from IT perspectives to elaborated knowledge concept (and first of all in the field of biodiversity, the status of a taxon specially). Their publication by each biodiversity database should be recommanded in order to accelerate their use and recognition within and outside the biodiversity community.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\nDBTNT family databases - as FLOW - follow the <A href='http://vocabularies.gbif.org/'>GBIF Vocabularies </A> and the <A href='http://vocabularies.gbif.org/biblio/Markus-D%C3%B6ring/2009'>\r\nDarwin Core Vocabularies</A> (published by Markus Döring, 08/03/2009). The <A href='http://www.tdwg.org/activities/darwincore/'