inc_phylogenie	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p>La phylogénie des Cercopoidea reste à ce jour pratiquement inexplorée. L’unique phylogénie publiée contenant des résultats pertinents sur l’évolution de ce groupe est une analyse phylogénétique du sous-ordre des Cicadomorphes (Cryan, 2005).</p>\r\n<p>Un soutien de la monophylie des familles Cercopidae et Aphrophoridae apparaît bien qu’il soit particulièrement faible pour les Aphrophoridae. La famille récemment décrite des Epipiygidae apparaît comme monophylétique et vient se placer dans les Aphrophoridae. Enfin la monophylie des clades Machaerotidae et Clastopteridae est soutenue.</p>\r\n<p>Une étude à plus grande échelle est bien sur nécessaire et des caractères moléculaires aussi bien que morphologiques devront être pris en compte.</p>\r\n</div>	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p>Up to this day the phylogeny of the Cercopoidea remains practically unexplored.The unique phylogeny published containing relevant results on the evolution of this group is a phylogenetic analysis of the Cicadomorpha sub-order (Cryan, 2005).</p>\r\n<p>The monophyly of the families Cercopidae et Aphrophoridae is supported although it is particularly weak for the Aphrophoridae. The recently described family Epipiygidae appears as monophyletic and comes to take place within the Aphrophoridae. Finally the monophyly of the clades Machaerotidae and Clastopteridae is supported.</p>\r\n<p>A study on a bigger scale is needed and morphological as well as molecular character should be taken into account.</p>\r\n</div>	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p>La filogenia de Cercopoidea queda a este d&iacute;a pr&aacute;cticamente inexplorado. El &uacute;nico filogenia publicado que contiene los resultados pertinentes sobre la evoluci&oacute;n de este grupo es un an&aacute;lisis filogenetico del suborden del Cicadomorpha (Cryan, 2005).</p>\r\n<p>Un sost&eacute;n della monofilia de las familias Cercopidae et Aphrophoridae aparece bien para que sea particularmente d&eacute;bil para Aphrophoridae. La familia recientemente descrita por Epipiygidae aparece como monofil&eacute;tica y viene para colocarse en Aphrophoridae. Por fin la monofilia del clades Machaerotidae y Clastopteridae es sostenido.</p>\r\n<p>Un estudio a escala m&aacute;s grande es bien sobre neceser y car&aacute;cteres moleculares tanto como morfol&oacute;gicos deber&aacute;n ser tomados en consideraci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n</div>	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p>Até o momento a filogenia de Cercopoidea continua praticamente inexplorada. A única filogenia publicada contendo resultados relevantes quanto à evolução do grupo é uma análise filogenética da sub-ordem Cicadomorpha (Cryan, 2005).</p>\r\n<p>A monofilia das famílias Cercopidae e Aphrophoridae é suportada, embora seja especialmente fraca para os Aphrophoridae. A família Epipiygidae aparece como monofilética e se anida dentro dos Aphrophoridae. Por fim, a monofilia dos clados Machaerotidae e Clastopteridae é suportada. </p>\r\n<p>Faz falta um estudo em maior escala, em que dados morfológicos e moleculares sejam levados em conta.</p>\r\n</div>	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p>Up to this day the phylogeny of the Cercopoidea remains practically unexplored.The unique phylogeny published containing relevant results on the evolution of this group is a phylogenetic analysis of the Cicadomorpha sub-order (Cryan, 2005).</p>\r\n<p>The monophyly of the families Cercopidae et Aphrophoridae is supported although it is particularly weak for the Aphrophoridae. The recently described family Epipiygidae appears as monophyletic and comes to take place within the Aphrophoridae. Finally the monophyly of the clades Machaerotidae and Clastopteridae is supported.</p>\r\n<p>A study on a bigger scale is needed and morphological as well as molecular character should be taken into account.</p>\r\n</div>	soulier	2011-04-14	bourgoin	2014-02-04	<script language="javascript">\r\nmenu('open');\r\n</script>\r\n<div id="<?php print($page); ?>">\r\n<p>Up to this day the phylogeny of the Cercopoidea remains practically unexplored.The unique phylogeny published containing relevant results on the evolution of this group is a phylogenetic analysis of the Cicadomorpha sub-order (Cryan, 2005).</p>\r\n<p>The monophyly of the families Cercopidae et Aphrophoridae is supported although it is particularly weak for the Aphrophoridae. The recently described family Epipiygidae appears as monophyletic and comes to take place within the Aphrophoridae. Finally the monophyly of the clades Machaerotidae and Clastopteridae is supported.</p>\r\n<p>A study on a bigger scale is needed and morphological as well as molecular character should be taken into account.</p>\r\n</div>
